Function to train models and evaluate performance

evaluate_models <- function(dataset_h2o, predictors, outcome) {

  # Convert the outcome to factor (for classification tasks)
  dataset_h2o[, outcome] <- as.factor(dataset_h2o[, outcome])
  
  # Logistic Regression
  logit_model <- h2o.glm(
    x = predictors, 
    y = outcome, 
    training_frame = dataset_h2o, 
    family = "binomial", 
    nfolds = 10, 
    seed = 1234
  )
  
  # Random Forest
  rf_model <- h2o.randomForest(
    x = predictors, 
    y = outcome, 
    training_frame = dataset_h2o, 
    nfolds = 10, 
    seed = 1234
  )
  
  # GBM
  gbm_model <- h2o.gbm(
    x = predictors, 
    y = outcome, 
    training_frame = dataset_h2o, 
    nfolds = 10, 
    seed = 1234
  )
  
  # Decision Tree (using H2O's Decision Tree)
  dt_model <- h2o.naiveBayes(  # Assuming Naive Bayes is replaced by DT if available
    x = predictors, 
    y = outcome, 
    training_frame = dataset_h2o, 
    nfolds = 10, 
    seed = 1234
  )
  
  # Neural Network (MLP with two hidden layers)
  nn_model <- h2o.deeplearning(
    x = predictors, 
    y = outcome, 
    training_frame = dataset_h2o, 
    hidden = c(64, 64), 
    activation = "RectifierWithDropout", 
    nfolds = 10, 
    seed = 1234
  )

  # Get Performance for each model at threshold = 0.5
  get_metrics <- function(model, dataset) {
    perf <- h2o.performance(model, dataset)
    auc <- h2o.auc(perf)
    aucpr <- h2o.aucpr(perf)
    
    # Get metrics at threshold = 0.5
    threshold_0.5 <- 0.5
    accuracy <- h2o.accuracy(perf, thresholds = threshold_0.5)
    precision <- h2o.precision(perf, thresholds = threshold_0.5)
    recall <- h2o.recall(perf, thresholds = threshold_0.5)
    f1 <- h2o.F1(perf, thresholds = threshold_0.5)
    
    list(auc = auc, aucpr = aucpr, precision = precision, recall = recall, accuracy = accuracy, f1 = f1)
  }
  
  # Store metrics for each model
  metrics <- list(
    logistic = get_metrics(logit_model, dataset_h2o),
    random_forest = get_metrics(rf_model, dataset_h2o),
    gbm = get_metrics(gbm_model, dataset_h2o),
    decision_tree = get_metrics(dt_model, dataset_h2o),
    neural_network = get_metrics(nn_model, dataset_h2o)
  )
  
  # Extract ROC and PR curves data for each model
  fpr_logit <- as.data.frame(h2o.fpr(h2o.performance(logit_model, dataset_h2o)))
  tpr_logit <- as.data.frame(h2o.tpr(h2o.performance(logit_model, dataset_h2o)))
  fpr_rf <- as.data.frame(h2o.fpr(h2o.performance(rf_model, dataset_h2o)))
  tpr_rf <- as.data.frame(h2o.tpr(h2o.performance(rf_model, dataset_h2o)))
  fpr_gbm <- as.data.frame(h2o.fpr(h2o.performance(gbm_model, dataset_h2o)))
  tpr_gbm <- as.data.frame(h2o.tpr(h2o.performance(gbm_model, dataset_h2o)))
  fpr_dt <- as.data.frame(h2o.fpr(h2o.performance(dt_model, dataset_h2o)))
  tpr_dt <- as.data.frame(h2o.tpr(h2o.performance(dt_model, dataset_h2o)))
  fpr_nn <- as.data.frame(h2o.fpr(h2o.performance(nn_model, dataset_h2o)))
  tpr_nn <- as.data.frame(h2o.tpr(h2o.performance(nn_model, dataset_h2o)))
  
  auc_logit <- round(h2o.auc(h2o.performance(logit_model, dataset_h2o)), 3)
auc_rf <- round(h2o.auc(h2o.performance(rf_model, dataset_h2o)), 3)
auc_gbm <- round(h2o.auc(h2o.performance(gbm_model, dataset_h2o)), 3)
auc_dt <- round(h2o.auc(h2o.performance(dt_model, dataset_h2o)), 3)
auc_nn <- round(h2o.auc(h2o.performance(nn_model, dataset_h2o)), 3)
  
  # Combine ROC data for ggplot
  roc_data <- rbind(
  data.frame(FPR = fpr_logit$fpr, TPR = tpr_logit$tpr, Model = paste("Logistic Regression (AUC:", auc_logit, ")")),
  data.frame(FPR = fpr_rf$fpr, TPR = tpr_rf$tpr, Model = paste("Random Forest (AUC:", auc_rf, ")")),
  data.frame(FPR = fpr_gbm$fpr, TPR = tpr_gbm$tpr, Model = paste("GBM (AUC:", auc_gbm, ")")),
  data.frame(FPR = fpr_dt$fpr, TPR = tpr_dt$tpr, Model = paste("Decision Tree (AUC:", auc_dt, ")")),
  data.frame(FPR = fpr_nn$fpr, TPR = tpr_nn$tpr, Model = paste("Neural Network (AUC:", auc_nn, ")"))
)
  
  # Plot ROC curves
  roc_plot <- ggplot(roc_data, aes(x = FPR, y = TPR, color = Model)) +
    geom_line(size = 1.2) +
    labs(title = "ROC Curve", x = "False Positive Rate (FPR)", y = "True Positive Rate (TPR)") +
    theme_minimal() +
    scale_color_manual(values = c("blue", "red", "green", "purple", "orange")) +
    theme(legend.position = c(0.8, 0.2))  # Legend inside
  
  # Combine PR data for ggplot
  precision_logit <- h2o.precision(h2o.performance(logit_model, dataset_h2o))
  recall_logit <- h2o.recall(h2o.performance(logit_model, dataset_h2o))
  precision_rf <- h2o.precision(h2o.performance(rf_model, dataset_h2o))
  recall_rf <- h2o.recall(h2o.performance(rf_model, dataset_h2o))
  precision_gbm <- h2o.precision(h2o.performance(gbm_model, dataset_h2o))
  recall_gbm <- h2o.recall(h2o.performance(gbm_model, dataset_h2o))
  precision_dt <- h2o.precision(h2o.performance(dt_model, dataset_h2o))
  recall_dt <- h2o.recall(h2o.performance(dt_model, dataset_h2o))
  precision_nn <- h2o.precision(h2o.performance(nn_model, dataset_h2o))
  recall_nn <- h2o.recall(h2o.performance(nn_model, dataset_h2o))
  
  aucpr_logit <- round(h2o.aucpr(h2o.performance(logit_model, dataset_h2o)), 3)
aucpr_rf <- round(h2o.aucpr(h2o.performance(rf_model, dataset_h2o)), 3)
aucpr_gbm <- round(h2o.aucpr(h2o.performance(gbm_model, dataset_h2o)), 3)
aucpr_dt <- round(h2o.aucpr(h2o.performance(dt_model, dataset_h2o)), 3)
aucpr_nn <- round(h2o.aucpr(h2o.performance(nn_model, dataset_h2o)), 3)

  pr_data <- rbind(
  data.frame(Recall = recall_logit$tpr, Precision = precision_logit$precision, Model = paste("Logistic Regression (AUCPR:", aucpr_logit, ")")),
  data.frame(Recall = recall_rf$tpr, Precision = precision_rf$precision, Model = paste("Random Forest (AUCPR:", aucpr_rf, ")")),
  data.frame(Recall = recall_gbm$tpr, Precision = precision_gbm$precision, Model = paste("GBM (AUCPR:", aucpr_gbm, ")")),
  data.frame(Recall = recall_dt$tpr, Precision = precision_dt$precision, Model = paste("Decision Tree (AUCPR:", aucpr_dt, ")")),
  data.frame(Recall = recall_nn$tpr, Precision = precision_nn$precision, Model = paste("Neural Network (AUCPR:", aucpr_nn, ")"))
)
  
  # Plot PR curves
  pr_plot <- ggplot(pr_data, aes(x = Recall, y = Precision, color = Model)) +
    geom_line(size = 1.2) +
    labs(title = "Precision-Recall Curve", x = "Recall", y = "Precision") +
    theme_minimal() +
    scale_color_manual(values = c("blue", "red", "green", "purple", "orange")) +
    theme(legend.position = c(0.8, 0.2))  # Legend inside
  
  # Return the metrics and the plots
  return(list(metrics = metrics, roc_plot = roc_plot, pr_plot = pr_plot))
}

Prediction Performance of model3 (baseline+socioeconomic+pdc90) after SMOTE (oversampling the minority class)

library(ggplot2) library(dplyr)

evaluate_models2 <- function(dataset_h2o, predictors, outcome = "discontinued") {
    # Convert the outcome to factor (for classification tasks)
    dataset_h2o[, outcome] <- as.factor(dataset_h2o[, outcome])
    
    # Set common parameters for SMOTE-like class balancing
    balance_params <- list(balance_classes = TRUE, class_sampling_factors = c(1.0, 3.57))  # 3.57 approximates the imbalance
    
    # Logistic Regression
    logit_model <- h2o.glm(
      x = predictors,
      y = outcome,
      training_frame = dataset_h2o,
      family = "binomial",
      nfolds = 10,
      seed = 1234,
      balance_classes = balance_params$balance_classes,
      class_sampling_factors = balance_params$class_sampling_factors  # Apply class balancing parameters
    )
    
    # Random Forest
    rf_model <- h2o.randomForest(
      x = predictors,
      y = outcome,
      training_frame = dataset_h2o,
      nfolds = 10,
      seed = 1234,
      balance_classes = balance_params$balance_classes,
      class_sampling_factors = balance_params$class_sampling_factors
    )
    
    # GBM
    gbm_model <- h2o.gbm(
      x = predictors,
      y = outcome,
      training_frame = dataset_h2o,
      nfolds = 10,
      seed = 1234,
      balance_classes = balance_params$balance_classes,
      class_sampling_factors = balance_params$class_sampling_factors
    )
    
    # Neural Network (MLP with two hidden layers)
    nn_model <- h2o.deeplearning(
      x = predictors,
      y = outcome,
      training_frame = dataset_h2o,
      hidden = c(64, 64),
      activation = "RectifierWithDropout",
      nfolds = 10,
      seed = 1234,
      balance_classes = balance_params$balance_classes,
      class_sampling_factors = balance_params$class_sampling_factors
    )
   
    
    # Get Performance for each model at threshold = 0.5
    get_metrics <- function(model, dataset) {
      perf <- h2o.performance(model, dataset)
      auc <- h2o.auc(perf)
      aucpr <- h2o.aucpr(perf)
      
      # Get metrics at threshold = 0.5
      threshold_0.5 <- 0.5
      accuracy <- h2o.accuracy(perf, thresholds = threshold_0.5)
      precision <- h2o.precision(perf, thresholds = threshold_0.5)
      recall <- h2o.recall(perf, thresholds = threshold_0.5)
      f1 <- h2o.F1(perf, thresholds = threshold_0.5)
      
      list(auc = auc, aucpr = aucpr, precision = precision, recall = recall, accuracy = accuracy, f1 = f1)
    }
    
    # Store metrics for each model
    metrics <- list(
      logistic = get_metrics(logit_model, dataset_h2o),
      random_forest = get_metrics(rf_model, dataset_h2o),
      gbm = get_metrics(gbm_model, dataset_h2o),
      neural_network = get_metrics(nn_model, dataset_h2o)
    )
    
    # Extract ROC and PR curves data for each model
    fpr_logit <- as.data.frame(h2o.fpr(h2o.performance(logit_model, dataset_h2o)))
    tpr_logit <- as.data.frame(h2o.tpr(h2o.performance(logit_model, dataset_h2o)))
    fpr_rf <- as.data.frame(h2o.fpr(h2o.performance(rf_model, dataset_h2o)))
    tpr_rf <- as.data.frame(h2o.tpr(h2o.performance(rf_model, dataset_h2o)))
    fpr_gbm <- as.data.frame(h2o.fpr(h2o.performance(gbm_model, dataset_h2o)))
    tpr_gbm <- as.data.frame(h2o.tpr(h2o.performance(gbm_model, dataset_h2o)))
    fpr_nn <- as.data.frame(h2o.fpr(h2o.performance(nn_model, dataset_h2o)))
    tpr_nn <- as.data.frame(h2o.tpr(h2o.performance(nn_model, dataset_h2o)))
    
    # Combine ROC data for ggplot
    roc_data <- rbind(
      data.frame(FPR = fpr_logit$fpr, TPR = tpr_logit$tpr, Model = "Logistic Regression"),
      data.frame(FPR = fpr_rf$fpr, TPR = tpr_rf$tpr, Model = "Random Forest"),
      data.frame(FPR = fpr_gbm$fpr, TPR = tpr_gbm$tpr, Model = "GBM"),
      data.frame(FPR = fpr_nn$fpr, TPR = tpr_nn$tpr, Model = "Neural Network")
    )
    
    # Plot ROC curves
    roc_plot <- ggplot(roc_data, aes(x = FPR, y = TPR, color = Model)) +
      geom_line(size = 1.2) +
      labs(title = "ROC Curve", x = "False Positive Rate (FPR)", y = "True Positive Rate (TPR)") +
      theme_minimal() +
      scale_color_manual(values = c("blue", "red", "green", "orange")) +
      theme(legend.position = c(0.8, 0.2))  # Legend inside
    
    # Combine PR data for ggplot
    precision_logit <- h2o.precision(h2o.performance(logit_model, dataset_h2o))
    recall_logit <- h2o.recall(h2o.performance(logit_model, dataset_h2o))
    precision_rf <- h2o.precision(h2o.performance(rf_model, dataset_h2o))
    recall_rf <- h2o.recall(h2o.performance(rf_model, dataset_h2o))
    precision_gbm <- h2o.precision(h2o.performance(gbm_model, dataset_h2o))
    recall_gbm <- h2o.recall(h2o.performance(gbm_model, dataset_h2o))
    precision_nn <- h2o.precision(h2o.performance(nn_model, dataset_h2o))
    recall_nn <- h2o.recall(h2o.performance(nn_model, dataset_h2o))
    
    pr_data <- rbind(
      data.frame(Recall = recall_logit$tpr, Precision = precision_logit$precision, Model = "Logistic Regression"),
      data.frame(Recall = recall_rf$tpr, Precision = precision_rf$precision, Model = "Random Forest"),
      data.frame(Recall = recall_gbm$tpr, Precision = precision_gbm$precision, Model = "GBM"),
      data.frame(Recall = recall_nn$tpr, Precision = precision_nn$precision, Model = "Neural Network")
    )
    
    # Plot PR curves
    pr_plot <- ggplot(pr_data, aes(x = Recall, y = Precision, color = Model)) +
      geom_line(size = 1.2) +
      labs(title = "Precision-Recall Curve", x = "Recall", y = "Precision") +
      theme_minimal() +
      scale_color_manual(values = c("blue", "red", "green", "orange")) +
      theme(legend.position = c(0.8, 0.2))  # Legend inside
    
    # Return the metrics and the plots
    return(list(metrics = metrics, roc_plot = roc_plot, pr_plot = pr_plot))
}

Virtual Twins Stage 2

library(rpart)
library(rpart.plot)

Function for stage 2

# Define the function
virtual_twins_analysis <- function(dataset, outcome, disparity_var, predictors1, predictors2) {
  # Step 1: Convert the dataset to H2O format
  dataset_h2o <- as.h2o(dataset) 
  
  # Split the dataset into 20% training and 80% testing
  splits <- h2o.splitFrame(data = dataset_h2o, ratios = 0.2, seed = 1234)
  train <- splits[[1]]  # 20% for training
  test <- splits[[2]]   # 80% for testing
  
  # Step 2: Train the Random Forest model using the training data
  rf_model_h2o <- h2o.randomForest(
    x = predictors1,
    y = outcome,
    training_frame = train,
    nfolds = 10,  # 10-fold cross-validation
    seed = 1234   # For reproducibility
  )

##h2o.varimp_plot(rf_model2_h2o, num_of_features = 20)
  
  # Step 3: Create two test datasets with "Low" and "High" disparity values
  data_L <- test
  data_H <- test
  data_L <- data_H <- h2o.assign(data_L, "data_L_h2o")
 # Set "0" and "1" disparity values as factors for both datasets
data_L[disparity_var] <- "0" 
data_H[disparity_var] <- "1" 
##data_H1<-as.data.frame(data_H) 
##table(data_H1$der_sex) 

data_L <- data_L[, !names(data_L) %in% outcome]
data_H <- data_H[, !names(data_H) %in% outcome]

  # Step 4: Predict probabilities for both datasets (Low and High disparity)
  pred_L <- h2o.predict(rf_model_h2o, data_L)
  pred_H <- h2o.predict(rf_model_h2o, data_H)
  
  # Convert predictions to data frames and extract probabilities
  probs_L <- as.data.frame(pred_L)$p1  # Assuming p1 is the probability of the positive class
  probs_H <- as.data.frame(pred_H)$p1
  
  # Step 5: Calculate Z = Prf(High) - Prf(Low)
  Z <- probs_H - probs_L
  
data_for_tree <- test
data_for_tree$Z <- as.h2o(Z) 

data_for_tree<-as.data.frame(data_for_tree)
  data_for_tree <- data_for_tree[, !names(data_for_tree) %in% c(outcome, disparity_var)] 
  
  # Step 7: Fit a regression tree with Z as the outcome and predictors as the features
  formula <- as.formula(paste("Z ~", paste(predictors2, collapse = " + ")))

  # Return the data_for_tree data frame and the formula for tree building
return(list(data_for_tree = data_for_tree, formula = formula)) 
}

Sex Disparities (Z = Prf(Sex=F, Xi) - Prf (Sex=M, Xi))

predictors1<- setdiff(names(episode_model33), "discontinued")
predictors2 <- c("pat_region", "age_group", "m_health", "nodrug", "alcohol", "svi", "telehealth", "induction", "outpatient", "bupre_tx", "hiv", "mat", "pay_type", "psychiatric") 
outcome <- "discontinued"
disparity_var <- "der_sex" 
# Call the function with the dataset and parameters
s2_result <- virtual_twins_analysis(
  dataset = episode_model34, 
  outcome = outcome, 
  disparity_var = disparity_var, 
  predictors1 = predictors1, 
  predictors2 = predictors2 
)
data_for_tree <- s2_result$data_for_tree
formula <- s2_result$formula

#par(mfrow = c(1, 2))
tree_model <- rpart(  
  formula, 
  data = data_for_tree, 
  method = "anova",
  control = rpart.control(
    minsplit = 75,  # Higher number to reduce splits
    cp = 0.002,      # Higher cp for aggressive pruning
    maxdepth = 3,   # Limit tree depth to 3 levels
    maxcompete = 0, # Prevent competing splits, to make splitting more strict
    maxsurrogate = 0 # Avoid using surrogate splits
  )
)
